description: ORDER GRANTING 8 Plaintiffs Kaylie Ray's, Macey Boggs', Sierra Grizzle's, Jordan Sandy's, Katelyn Van Kirk's, and Kiersten Van Kirk's Unopposed Motion for Leave to File an Emergency Motion for a Preliminary Injunction in Excess of Fifteen Pages (Motion). Plaintiffs may file their Motion not exceeding 35 pages in length, excluding the case caption, table of contents, signature block, certificate of service, certificate of conferral, and artificial intelligence certificate and accompanying exhibits.Further, the Court understands that Plaintiffs' anticipated Motion will seek relief related to the 2024 Mountain West Conference women's volleyball tournament set to begin on 11/27/2024. In consideration of the potentially short time frame in which to attempt to address the anticipated Motion, the Court FURTHER ORDERS the following:1) Plaintiffs' anticipated Motion shall be filed on or before 11/15/2024;2) Any response opposing the Motion shall be filed on or before 11/19/2024;3) Any response brief shall not exceed 35 pages in length, excluding the case caption, table of contents, signature block, certificate of service, certificate of conferral, and artificial intelligence certificate and accompanying exhibits; and4) No reply brief is permitted without leave of Court.The Court anticipates, if it orders a hearing on the Motion, it will set a one day, in-person hearing to occur on 11/21/2024 at 8:00am, by separate order. SO ORDERED by Judge S. Kato Crews on 11/15/2024. Text Only Entry (Entered: 11/15/2024)
